OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1778793068
OL,3,C'Not foreseeable' someone would enter
OL,4,Cculvert where Noah Donohoe's body found
OL,6,FNoah, a pupil at St Malachy's College,
OL,7,Fwas 14 when his naked body was found
OL,8,Fin an underground water tunnel in
OL,9,Fnorth Belfast on June 27 2020, six
OL,10,Fdays after he left home on his bike to
OL,11,Fmeet two friends in the Cavehill area
OL,12,Fof the city.
OL,14,FHe was found more than 600 metres
OL,15,Fdownstream from where he had last been
OL,16,Fseen close to the culvert inlet behind
OL,17,Fhouses at Northwood Road in north
OL,18,FBelfast.
OL,20,FA post-mortem examination found the
OL,21,Flikely cause of death was drowning.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1778793068
OL,3,C'Not foreseeable' someone would enter
OL,4,Cculvert where Noah Donohoe's body found
OL,6,FThe long-running inquest, which is in
OL,7,Fits 15th week, heard further evidence
OL,8,Ffrom DfI official Mr McKee on
OL,9,FWednesday.
OL,11,FHe was questioned by Neasa Murnaghan
OL,12,FKC, barrister for the DfI, about
OL,13,Fwhether it would have been possible to
OL,14,Ferect a fence between four houses on
OL,15,FNorthwood Road and the area of land
OL,16,Fwhere the culvert is located.
OL,18,FMr McKee said that would have been
OL,19,Fpotentially "cutting off access" for
OL,20,Fthose homeowners to an area of land
OL,21,Fwhich was not owned by the department.
OL,26,@{D@MOU{D@`O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1778793068
OL,3,C'Not foreseeable' someone would enter
OL,4,Cculvert where Noah Donohoe's body found
OL,6,FMs Murnaghan asked it if was
OL,7,F"reasonably foreseeable a trespasser
OL,8,Fwould have accessed" the area.
OL,10,FMr McKee said: "I don't believe so. It
OL,11,Fis not a publicly accessible piece of
OL,12,Fland, it is bounded by security
OL,13,Ffencing and a locked gate across its
OL,14,Fboundaries.
OL,16,F"There are hedging and fencing at one
OL,17,Fof the other boundaries and then there
OL,18,Fare four residential properties on the
OL,19,Fother boundary.
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@TO]rD@POUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1778793068
OL,3,C'Not foreseeable' someone would enter
OL,4,Cculvert where Noah Donohoe's body found
OL,6,F"I have been on this piece of land
OL,7,Fquite a few times and it is certainly
OL,8,Fa vigilant community.
OL,10,F"You don't feel you have the right to
OL,11,Fbe there, you feel you are on
OL,12,Fsomeone's property.
OL,14,F"The only reason I am able to go on is
OL,15,Fthe legal powers associated with the
OL,16,Fdepartment undertaking their
OL,17,Fresponsibilities, you can be on
OL,18,Fprivate land.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1778793068
OL,3,C'Not foreseeable' someone would enter
OL,4,Cculvert where Noah Donohoe's body found
OL,6,F"It wouldn't have been, in my view, an
OL,7,Farea of land where it would have been
OL,8,Fforeseeable for someone to come on to
OL,9,Fthe houses, enter into their gardens
OL,10,Fand then cross over that boundary
OL,11,Ffence or through a gate into this area
OL,12,Fof land."
OL,14,FThe barrister asked the witness about
OL,15,Foptions the department could have
OL,16,Ftaken to reduce risks of access to the
OL,17,Fculvert.
OL,19,FHe said: "It is not always possible to
OL,20,Fmanage the risk associated with
OL,21,Finfrastructure down to zero.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@IO]{D@JOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1778793068
OL,3,C'Not foreseeable' someone would enter
OL,4,Cculvert where Noah Donohoe's body found
OL,6,F"Guidance is the tool to balance the
OL,7,Frisks that exist.
OL,9,F"Fencing wasn't a practicable option."
OL,11,FThe witness said there were a number
OL,12,Fof deterrents, including the barred
OL,13,Fdebris screen over the entrance to the
OL,14,Fculvert.
OL,16,FHe said: "I myself wondered could I
OL,17,Fget through the debris screen. I tried
OL,18,Fto do that and I couldn't."
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@AOUqD@fO]xD@JOUzD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1778793068
OL,3,C'Not foreseeable' someone would enter
OL,4,Cculvert where Noah Donohoe's body found
OL,6,FMs Murnaghan asked: "In all of your
OL,7,Fexperience have you ever come across a
OL,8,Fdeath which has arisen in these
OL,9,Fcircumstances."
OL,11,FMr McKee responded: "No."
OL,13,FThe witness said there could be
OL,14,F"significant waterflows" within the
OL,15,Fculvert.
OL,17,FHe said: "The stream is idyllic many
OL,18,Fdays of the year but there are times
OL,19,Fduring storms when the water level
OL,20,Fwould rise significantly and pose a
OL,21,Freal significant threat of entrapment.
OL,26,@nD@UOUqD@OO]sD@UOUsD@YO]vD@AOUvD@XO]yD@
OL,26,AJOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
